{% call components.section("Style") -%}
  <p>A default blockquote consists of three required elements, a quote icon, text, and attribution. It can be left- or center-aligned on large and small screens. A left-aligned blockquote can also feature additional elements, like large text styles and components on top or to the right whereas a center-aligned blockquote can’t include anything else.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote ">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote">The default blockquote includes only these three required elements.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote ">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote">Only the left-aligned blockquote can include these additional elements.</p>

  <h3>Theme</h3>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h3>Quote icon</h3>
  <p>A red quote icon is always placed above the quote text in both themes.</p>

  <h3>Attribution</h3>
  <p>A blockquote always has attribution text underneath that gives credit to whoever the quote is from.</p>

  <h3>Additional elements</h3>
  <p>A left-aligned blockquote can feature additional elements on top, like large text styles or a logo. If these optional elements are used, a thin vertical bar is added to the left of a blockquote to maintain focus with readers. These additional elements can be used without including a component to the right.</p>

    {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
      <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote">
    </div>
    {%- endcall %}
    <p class="footnote">(Other dropdown option: Logo)</p>
{%- endcall %}

<hr class="margin-top--10 margin-bottom--10">

{% call components.section("Usage") -%}
  <h3>Layout</h3>
  <p>The width of a blockquote on large screens is determined by alignment and if they’re used with a component. For more information about layout configurations, see Layout <!-- future link-->. </p>
  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote">When used on its own or with large text styles or a logo on top, a left-aligned blockquote is seven grid columns wide.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote">A center-aligned blockquote is eight grid columns wide and can’t be used with other components.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote">When used with a <a href="../card">Card</a>, a left-aligned blockquote is seven grid columns wide (7-1-4 layout).</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="inline-flex margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
    <img src="{{ 'http://www.placehold.it/652x141' | url }}" alt="Example of blockquote">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}
  <p class="footnote">When used with a <a href="../video-thumbnail">Video thumbnail</a>, a left-aligned blockquote is five grid columns (5-1-6 layout).</p>
{%- endcall %}

